OL,7,FJane, who worked as a paediatric
OL,8,Fconsultant for 30 years, is convinced
OL,9,Fher son's experience in an adult unit
OL,10,Fwas responsible for him failing to
OL,11,Ftalk with health professionals in the
OL,12,Ffinal months of his life.
OL,14,FShe said: "He was never the same boy
OL,15,Fagain. He found it difficult to attend
OL,16,Fappointments, he gave very little
OL,17,Faway, he was guarded. I think his
OL,18,Freluctance to engage was really fear
OL,19,Fto engage with them from that point
OL,20,Fonwards.
OL,26,@vD@KOU
